Detailed Description

Vector containing pointers to SubRoutes.

The class is used by RouteSender and RouteObject to manipulate SubRoutes towards what will be the finished route. The class inherits from SubRouteVector Useful functions inherited from SubRouteVector are: void resetIndex(uint32 index) : Resets the pointer at a specified index. uint32 getSize() const : Returns the number of elements in the vector SubRoute* getSubRouteAt(uint32 index) const : Asks for the SubRoute on a certain position in the vector Note that there is no way of dequeueing from this class. To access members that you do not want to remain in the vector, use 'getSubRouteAt' and then 'resetIndex'

uint32 ServerSubRouteVector::getCutOff (   )  const
 

Returns the greatest of the costs to get to a destination if we should return the routes to all destinations.

Returns the cheapest cost to one destination if this is the last part of the (via)route. Currently contains a cheat that removes a lot of the dests if we have too few reached destinations. This way we will get a cutoff faster. MAX_UINT32 if we have not reached all dests yet.
